            <h2>Parallelogram formulas used</h2>
            <div class="formula-box text-sm">
              <p><strong>Area (base & height):</strong> \( A = b \cdot h \)</p>
              <p><strong>Area (sides & angle):</strong> \( A = a \cdot b \cdot \sin(\theta) \)</p>
              <p><strong>Perimeter:</strong> \( P = 2(a + b) \)</p>
              <p><strong>Height (relative to a):</strong> \( h = b \cdot \sin(\theta) \)</p>
              <p><strong>Diagonals:</strong> \( d_1 = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2 - 2ab\cos(\theta)} \), \( d_2 = \sqrt{a^2 + b^2 + 2ab\cos(\theta)} \)</p>
              <p><strong>Area (diagonals & angle φ):</strong> \( A = \frac{d_1 d_2 \sin(\varphi)}{2} \)</p>
            </div>

