              <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-800">Why is the perimeter missing in the diagonals tab?</summary>
                <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">To compute the perimeter we need at least one side length. Provide side a in the field labeled “Optional side a.”</p>
              </details>
              <details class="border border-gray-200 rounded-md p-3">
                <summary class="cursor-pointer font-medium text-gray-800">When is a parallelogram a rhombus or a rectangle?</summary>
                <p class="mt-2 text-gray-600">A rhombus has all sides equal. A rectangle has 90° angles. If both are true, it’s a square. The calculator shows a note when it detects these patterns.</p>
